We have recommended that the Municipal Mayor expedite the implementation of the 20% DF projects. In addition, we recommended that the Municipal Mayor:

Require the Bids and Awards Committee in coordination with the office of the Municipal Engineer to advertise the procurement of small value projects on a per package basis (e.g. 1 to 5 small projects) to entice licensed contractors to participate in the bidding;


Ensure that projects included in the 20% Development Fund are free from  RROW problems, and donated lots are secured and processed in the name of the Municipality to avoid problems during project implementation;


Require the Municipal Planning and Development Officer and Municipal Engineer to revisit all unimplemented projects to determine if the projects are still feasible taking into consideration the amount of appropriation as compared to the present cost of implementing the project (reiteration of prior years’ audit recommendation) and recommend to the Municipal Development Council for the reversion thereof; 

Require the Municipal Budget Officer to determine savings from all implemented 20% Development Fund Projects and recommend to the LCE for its reversion to un-appropriated surplus for re-appropriation to other priority development projects; and

Direct the Municipal Treasurer and Municipal Budget Officer to include in the succeeding annual/supplemental budget the reverted funds from unimplemented projects and savings from implemented projects to fund other priority development projects and services.

