We have recommended and management agreed to:
a) prepare a thorough study and evaluation of the LGU’s needs for additional personnel to avoid excessive hiring of JOs;
b) direct the Department Heads and their permanent regular staff to perform efficiently the duties assigned to their office and not to depend on job order personnel;
c) decrease the budget for wages of job order personnel of the different departments and instead use the amount to provide basic services for the majority of the constituents; and
d) limit the hiring of personnel through contracts of service, only for essential and necessary activities of approved local projects; and
e) specify in the appointments the project and activities to be undertaken which are measurable to facilitate comparison with the accomplishments of each JO.
